some of the american hostages who are 
spending a quiet but somber thanksgiving in the iraqi capital say 
it could be worse they could be among the human shields held 
at potential military targets 
although we have it better than those at the sites we all 
suffer the indignity of being a hostage said roland bergheer 
among a handful of american men who planned a turkey dinner today 
at the us embassy residence 
about 100 americans are among the 600 westerners held at 
strategic iraqi installations to deter a feared us attack 
everyone at the residence feels this is the greatest holiday 
of the year the most meaningful but it will be somber and 
quiet said bergheer 62 a construction company executive who 
grew up in los angeles and makes his home in las vegas 
joe wilson the charge daffaires at the american embassy said 
he hoped to begin thanksgiving with the latest of several protests 
to the iraqi foreign ministry about the plight of americans 
prevented from leaving iraq 
it is an issue that wilson has raised at least twice a week with 
officials at all levels and with president saddam hussein during 
their only meeting on aug 6 four days after iraqs invasion of 
kuwait 
he said special appeals have been made for hostages with medical 
problems and individuals who should be evacuated for humanitarian 
reasons wilson said 75 people fall into those categories 
the iraqis have mostly ignored the appeals even for one man 
whose wife died while he was being held at a strategic site 
i tell you it is terribly frustrating wilson said i 
dont even know if my condolence letter to the gentleman has 
reached him 
he said the iraqi response has been that the hostages are 
guests who will be released when iraq receives assurances it 
will not be attacked 
diplomats are not allowed to visit hostages at strategic sites 
the embassy tries to send the hostages their mail through the 
foreign ministry the diplomats have set up a pen pal system in 
hopes of sending those hostages more regular mail they publish a 
weekly newsletter with football scores and news items designed not 
to attract the attention of an iraqi censor 
we try to give them something that will remind them of home 
and let them know we are thinking about them wilson said 
over the months of captivity the hostages in baghdad have 
developed close relationships among themselves and with the 
diplomats 
they the hostages are really tough people wilson said 
theyre good people they understand the issues and know how big 
the issues are they want to be able to walk out of here with 
their heads high and not as a result of some underhanded 
negotiations or payoff 
the american hostages in iraq on wednesday addressed a 
thanksgiving message to those celebrating the national holiday in 
the united states the message said in part 
the ingredients of this deeply meaningful dinner are very 
special and are not available everywhere the two main ingredients 
are freedom and justice for all freedom to be your very best to 
exceed your own expectations to worship and follow your own god 
and to come and go as you please justice to guarantee your rights 
and freedoms under our constitution until proven wrong 
