american hostages held in iraq have 
addressed a thanksgiving message to those celebrating the national 
holiday in the united states following is the text as released to 
foreign reporters 
on this most traditional of american holidays we would like 
to extend our best wishes to all the iraqis and iraqiamericans who 
are about to enjoy our national feast while in our country the 
united states of america 
the ingredients of this deeply meaningful dinner are very 
special and are not available everywhere the two main ingredients 
are freedom and justice for all freedom to be your very best to 
exceed your own expectations to worship and follow your own god 
and to come and go as you please justice to guarantee your rights 
and freedoms under our constitution until proven wrong 
so please sit down with your families and friends and enjoy 
this very special meal take a bite and savor the flavor of 
liberty eat plenty and enjoy it will be the finest meal youll 
ever have 
this is a meal that only an american can fully appreciate 
unfortunately we are not free to enjoy the full flavor of our 
thanksgiving meal while being held in iraq against our will 
signed american hostages baghdad 
