<TEXT>
information that helped china develop a 
neutron bomb was stolen from lawrence livermore national laboratory 
through espionage according to a published report 
a lab official who spoke on the condition of anonymity told the 
san jose mercury news that espionage sometime before 1987 gave the 
chinese information they needed to explode a neutron bomb on sept 
29 1988 
the official said the information leak was a result of total 
complete lack of management oversight 
details of how the information was passed remain classified 
george carver a former deputy director of the cia said 
publicly last month that the chinese success was based on us 
nuclear research the newspaper reported wednesday 
in 1988 the chinese blossomed forth with the neutron bomb 
which was made from data stolen from us research centers he 
said in a speech to lawrence livermore employees 
thats what a number of people think including my friends in 
the bureau fbi carter said in a telephone interview from his 
office at the center for strategic and international studies in 
washington dc 
ed appel the head of counterintelligence in the fbis san 
francisco office confirmed the bureau has investigated possible 
espionage at the lab no arrests have been made 
you could make the logical assumption that there have been 
successful espionage attempts against the lab since its 
inception appel said 
the general accounting office reported in 1988 that foreign 
intelligence agents posing as visiting scientists had gained access 
to lawrence livermore and americas other two nuclear weapons 
design laboratories 
the gao said dozens of chinese had visited lawrence livermore 
without a required background check and some were later found to 
have links to chinese intelligence services 
the chinese likely lacked information on how to build parts for 
a neutron bomb said john lewis a chinese affairs expert at 
stanford university 
its not a very difficult theoretical technology its an 
engineering problem said lewis who has written a book on the 
chinese nuclear weapons program 
a neutron bomb is a weapon designed to kill with lethal doses of 
radiation without the widespread damage caused by other nuclear 
weapons 
</TEXT>
