<TEXT>
a federal judge plans a dec 4 hearing on a 
lawsuit by 45 house democrats seeking to bar president bush from 
ordering an attack on iraq without congressional approval 
us district judge harold h greene on wednesday gave the 
government until monday to file its response to the lawsuit the 
judge said he would hear arguments dec 4 on the lawmakers motion 
for a preliminary injunction in the case 
the lawmakers led by rep ronald v dellums dcalif contend 
