the army has decided to halt retirements and 
discharges as well as transfers unrelated to the persian gulf 
crisis according to news reports 
the washington post said in todays editions that the army had 
decided to use the authority to hold personnel in the service 
which was granted by defense secretary dick cheney under a 
littlenoticed presidential order issued in august 
normally 5 percent to 7 percent of the 760000 soldiers in the 
army would leave each month 
the post said details of the plans were being worked out and 
that some exemptions would be given for hardship cases such as 
family illness the plan could keep in place most of the army 
personnel who may be seeking to return to the united states from 
overseas bases or move from one base to another the paper said 
