junk bond king michael milken credited with 
fueling wall streets corporate takeover boom of the 1980s now 
personifies americas change in fortunes with his 10year sentence 
for securities fraud 
it was the toughest penalty imposed in cases arising from the 
the wall street scandals that followed the boom 
the sentence us district judge kimba wood levied wednesday 
could be reduced if milken cooperates fully with prosecutors but 
the stiff term undercut criticism from milken supporters who 
claimed his crimes were merely technical violations 
