buildup of us forces in saudi arabia 
iraqi president saddam hussein sent his foreign minister tariq 
aziz to yemen on tuesday to deliver a message on the gulf 
situation according to the official yemeni news agency 
officials said baker would return to jiddah tonight and might 
meet friday with malaysian officials malaysia located on the 
southeastern tip of asia also is a member of the security council 
since last weekend baker has met with the foreign ministers of 
eight nations on the council next weekend he pays a visit to 
colombia where he will confer with president cesar gaviria 
baker said wednesday the united states and the soviet union had 
unanimity of opinion with regard to the problems in the gulf 
baker held lengthy meetings with soviet foreign minister eduard 
shevardnadze in paris this week during the 34nation summit of the 
conference on security and cooperation in europe 
shevardnadze had said in paris that the security council should 
take stock of things and if need be adopt new resolutions 
however neither he nor gorbachev endorsed the idea of a resolution 
to authorize use of force 
the security council has approved 10 resolutions against iraq 
since its aug 2 invasion of its oilrich neighbor they impose an 
economic boycott on iraq and occupied kuwait call for iraqs 
unconditional withdrawal and insist upon restoration of kuwaits 
previous government 
yemen has abstained from voting on half of those according to a 
state department count 
none of the resolutions authorizes military action but they 
leave the door open to other measures if iraq fails to respond to 
the steps 
