<TEXT>
margaret thatcher has been every bit the iron lady 
durable rigid formidable in battle 
since taking power in 1979 as britains first woman prime 
minister mrs thatcher has often been unpopular often a minority 
in britains alliances and even in her own cabinet and never 
in doubt 
but on thursday she announced her resignation amid a strong 
leadership challenge from her former defense minister michael 
heseltine 
only winston churchill rivaled mrs thatchers commanding 
profile in 20th century britain and no one approached her record 
of three straight general election victories 
in 1980 when others shirked from the radical freemarket cures 
of thatcherism mrs thatcher scolded her fellow conservatives 
you turn if you want to the ladys not for turning 
she dismantled britains version of socialism crushed 
obstructive labor unions led a military victory against argentina 
in the falkland islands and preached military readiness to the 
western alliance 
asked what she had changed in her country her answer was 
simple everything 
we have raised britain in the respect of the world from what 
it was broke bankrupt unwilling to defend itself properly 
she said in 1987 we have i think transformed britain 
in the 1980s thenpresident ronald reagan was her friend and 
ideological soulmate but she was one of the first western leaders 
to recognize soviet president mikhail s gorbachev as someone we 
can do business with 
even before she became prime minister the soviet press had 
tagged her as the iron lady a title she wore proudly 
a political outsider mrs thatcher was proud of imposing the 
values she had learned from her father a smalltown grocer on a 
political establishment grounded in wealth and privilege 
she led the conservative party to election victories without 
ever winning the affection of most of her people throughout her 
career she was fortunate in her opponents 
she was elected party leader on may 4 1975 ousting edward 
heath after he had lost two national elections in a row 
in 1979 her election was insured by popular disgust with high 
inflation and labor unrest under the labor party government 
when her own popularity ebbed in 1982 argentina invaded the 
falklands the surge of national pride that followed the reconquest 
carried her triumphantly through the 1983 election 
she was also helped by the split in the labor party which 
produced a new party of the center so that the conservatives won 
elections without winning majorities of the popular vote 
after the collapse of the iron curtain when her gospel of 
military preparedness began to appear passe iraqi president saddam 
hussein invaded kuwait on aug 2 once again she was the best 
friend of an american president backing up tough talk with ships 
tanks and troops 
the political left loathed her and had good reason to fear her 
liberals accused her of exacerbating divisions between rich and 
poor and of undermining free speech 
peter jenkins a leading liberal columnist said after a decade 
of thatcherism that she had overthrown the existing order 
changed the political map and put her country on its feet again 
she did all this with ruthlessness and much injustice and at a 
high cost in human misery but she did it commented jenkins 
for the majority who had jobs she raised living standards 
dramatically average earnings were up by nearly onethird and 
more britons owned their homes 
thatcherism was all about free markets and private enterprise 
she sold much of the industry the labor government had 
nationalized turning such moneylosers as steel and british 
airways into profitable enterprises 
her success deeply affected the labor party which moved sharply 
to the center in hope of regaining power 
to her admirers battling maggie was a national savior who ended 
britains postwar cycle of confrontation and decline to her 
detractors she was an antiunion bull set free in a china shop 
destroying revered institutions 
in 1981 after she began implementing her rigorous policies and 
unemployment soared to a record 3 million mrs thatcher was rated 
the most unpopular prime minister since opinion polls began 
even when she had become a sort of national institution polls 
regularly indicated twothirds of britons disliked her personally 
similar majorities also said they respected her and courage was 
one of the qualities they admired 
she survived unscathed from an irish republican army bomb that 
killed five people at the 1984 party convention in brighton 
you have to cope with it she said because if you didnt 
and they intimidated you out of doing the work you have been 
elected to do it would be the end of democracy 
in foreign policy britain under mrs thatcher was unequivocally 
proamerican 
in 1986 she was alone among the allies in associating herself 
with the us bombing of libya allowing the bombers to fly from 
british bases 
when the iron curtain crumbled in 1989 and a united germany 
emerged as europes new superpower mrs thatcher appeared 
sidelined 
but she reemerged as the leader most willing to rush to 
americas side with troops in the persian gulf crisis 
mrs thatcher fought mighty battles with fellow european 
community leaders resisting attempts to turn the community into a 
sort of united states of europe 
born oct 13 1925 margaret hilda roberts learned her values of 
thrift discipline and industry from her father a grocer in the 
small town of grantham in central england 
she became involved in politics at oxford university where she 
won a chemistry degree in 1947 
her electoral career began in the traditional way slogging 
through hopeless campaigns in 1950 and 1951 in districts where the 
conservatives had no hope 
she married wealth businessman denis thatcher in 1951 and their 
twins carol and mark came two years later 
mrs thatcher was elected to parliament in 1958 for finchley a 
middleclass north london district she was minister of pensions 
and national insurance from 196163 under prime ministers harold 
macmillan and lord home edward heath made her education secretary 
in his cabinet of 197074 
against formidable odds including her social origins and her 
sex she won a contest for the party leadership in 1975 w 
hile more prominent conservatives held back from a challenge 
mrs thatcher plunged in winning so many votes in the first round 
that heath resigned 
the 1975 party election was the start of what biographer hugo 
young called an era in which an ordinary politician laboring 
under many disadvantages grew into an international figure who did 
some extraordinary things to her country 
</TEXT>
