the washington institute for near east policy 
if it receives help from abroad it could be producing 
nuclear weapons within as little as five years said eisenstadt 
who also serves as a civilian analyst for us army intelligence 
the iraqi program got its start with help from france which 
sold two nuclear reactors to baghdad in 1976 for the production of 
electricity 
but israel citing intelligence information said iraq was using 
the reactors to produce nuclear weapons with the help of 150 pounds 
of enriched uranium supplied by france 
the substance is essential for exploding nuclear weapons and 
israel has reportedly obtained sufficient amounts to produce its 
own nuclear arsenal 
in 1981 israeli fighter planes bombed the iraqi nuclear 
facility outside baghdad israel drew international condemnation 
but the iraqi program was brought to a standstill 
the enriched uranium that was left over from the french shipment 
estimated at about 27 pounds was placed under the safeguards 
program of the nuclear nonproliferation treaty of which iraq is a 
signatory 
that means inspectors from the viennabased international atomic 
energy agency periodically inspect the material to make sure iraq 
isnt diverting it for weapons production 
the next inspection is scheduled next week and although the 
results generally remain classified us experts have said iraqs 
willingness to allow the inspection indicates it has not diverted 
the material 
nonetheless state department officials say iraq could have 
acquired other uranium which is not under the inspection program 
in the late 1970s and early 1980s according to eisenstadts 
report iraq acquired 250 tons of uranium ore concentrate from 
brazil portugal and niger this material is not weaponsgrade but 
could have been used to extract plutonium another essential 
component in a nuclear weapon said eisenstadt 
in 1987 iraq revived its nuclear program experts say 
rather than rebuilding the bombed reactor iraq decided to 
acquire a gas centrifuge device for enriching uranium according to 
experts and press reports brazil and pakistan both burgeoning 
nuclear powers have reportedly used this method successfully but 
it took each of them about a decade to have operational 
centrifuges 
iraq could use the uranium ore concentrate which is not subject 
to iaea inspection to power the centrifuge which produces enriched 
uranium experts say 
work on the iraqi project is reportedly being conducted at the 
saad 16 facility near the city of mosul at another site in a 
mountain near irbil and at the tuwaitha nuclear center outside 
baghdad 
west german firms taking advantage of their countrys formerly 
loose export restriction laws were instrumental in helping iraqs 
gas centrifuge project so were china pakistan and 
inadvertently several american and british firms 
last year us customs agents seized vacuum pumps bound for 
iraq from a rochester ny company saying the iraqis could have 
used them in their nuclear program 
british customs agents acting on a tip from us officials 
earlier this year seized a shipment of krytons to iraq krytons are 
used to detonate nuclear weapons 
after the seizure saddam announced his country could produce 
the devices on its own 
in addition to the concentrate uranium known as yellowcake 
iraq may also be trying to extract the metal from a mine in the 
northern part of the country 
recent soviet satellite pictures have found an industrial 
operation including new roads and two excavation sites in the 
gara mountains 40 miles south of the turkish border according to 
the respected janes defense weekly 
</TEXT>
