<TEXT>
britain announced thursday it was nearly doubling 
its troops deployed in the persian gulf sending 14000 more 
soldiers to join the 16000 already in the region 
prime minister margaret thatcher moved to send more troops to 
the gulf on thursday at the same cabinet meeting at which she was 
warned she would lose her bid for the party leadership and thus 
leadership of the country she later announced her resignation 
mrs thatcher has been an implacable opponent of iraqs takeover 
of kuwait and her party indicated her policies in the gulf would 
be continued 
former defense minister michael heseltine who challenged mrs 
thatcher for the party leadership and prompted her resignation 
expressed his firm support for the new deployment 
it was essential that the military capablity of the british 
force have total credibilty he said the announcement you have 
made this afternoon carries the wholehearted and unanimous 
support of all conservatives 
the new deployments would make the british troop commitment to 
the multinational forces in the region the secondlargest behind 
the united states which has sent 250000 and promised another 
100000 
defense secretary tom king went before the house of commons to 
explain the deployment 
it remains the governments firm objective to resolve this 
crisis as soon as possible and by peaceful means he told 
lawmakers to do this it is essential to establish a credible 
offensive military option 
saddam hussein must be made to realize that he is faced with a 
military force that will otherwise compel him to withdraw king 
said 
at least 26 nations have contributed troops to the multinational 
effort to force iraq out of kuwait which saddam hussein invaded 
aug 2 in a dispute over land oil and money 
the additional troops bring the strength of the 1st army 
division to 25000 and total british forces committed to the gulf 
to 30000 king said 
the 4th brigade currently stationed in germany division 
headquarters and supporting arms will join the 9500strong 7th 
armored brigade to form the 1st armored division he said 
the additional brigade will include an armored regiment of 
challenger tanks two armored infantry battions with warrior 
fighting vehicles an armored reconnaissance squadron a royal 
artillery field regiment engineers and other supporting services 
the government is sending antitank lynx helicopters and the 
armys most potent artillery system the multiple launch rocket 
system king said 
the system is capable of rapid fire over long range and will be 
able to counter iraqs g5 howitzers 
king said he discussed the new troop deployment in meetings last 
week with saudi arabias king fahd who welcomed the news and 
offered to help provide food fuel trnsport and accomodations 
the announcement coincided with the resignation of prime 
minister margaret thatcher who sat behind king as he addressed the 
house of commons there was concern that britains domestic 
political problems not damage the effort to drive iraqi occupation 
forces from kuwait 
