prime minister margaret thatcher called it quits 
thursday leaving her nation transformed by 11 years of 
thatcherism and her party torn by a bitter and potentially 
destructive struggle for succession 
the iron lady informed her cabinet of her decision to resign 
the morning after she declared she would fight on to a second 
round of the leadership election against former defense minister 
michael heseltine 
she told us of her decision and then got on with business 
said transport secretary cecil parkinson at the same cabinet 
meeting she decided to commit 14000 more british troops to the 
persian gulf 
as flowers and tributes poured into the official residence at 10 
downing street she passionately defended her government against a 
motion of noconfidence introduced by labor party leader neil 
kinnock 
im enjoying this im enjoying this she shouted in the 
house of commons full to overflowing for a sometimes rude 
sometimes sentimental debate a tiredlooking mrs thatcher was 
sometimes hoarse and frequently coughed 
the motion of censure which could have brought down the 
government was resoundingly defeated by a 120vote majority in the 
650seat house late thursday with no tory defectors 
no longer shackled by loyalty foreign secretary douglas hurd 
and treasury chief john major earlier thursday quickly jumped into 
the leadership contest which will be settled next week thursday 
was the deadline for nominations 
after succeeding laborite james callaghan as prime minister in 
1979 mrs thatcher relentlessly promoted capitalism in britain 
she sold many nationalized industries to private shareholders 
including british steel and british airways crushed the power of 
labor unions and cut tax rates 
by directing a risky but successful war against argentina in the 
falklands in 1982 and through her close relationship with president 
ronald reagan she was widely credited with restoring britains 
selfimage as a world power 
at home the party rebellion had been building for years but 
news that margaret thatcher walked away from a fight surprised the 
world 
