thursday it will close next week making it the ninth major victim 
in portugals collapsing press market 
on wednesday the lisbon evening paper diario de lisboa said it 
will fold nov 30 
they will bring to nine the number of major daily and weekly 
papers to shut down since the end of a press boom in the late 
1980s when a crop of new publications hit the stands investors 
had hoped for advertising revenue in one of europes fastest 
growing economies 
but the market was unable to sustain the increasing number of 
papers in a country where almost 20 percent of the 103 million 
people are illiterate 
the weekly tempo was founded in 1975 as a conservative voice 
