kevin paxton has worked at the teledyne cae 
plant for more than 10 years he says he was a company man who took 
pride in his work as a tool and die maker 
but when the 35yearold father of two thinks of teledyne these 
days he feels mostly anger and bitterness over a 10month strike 
that has cast a pall over the holiday season 
you do a good job for the company and you want to continue on 
but they seem like they just dont care that hurts i mean i feel 
like my legs have been kicked out from under me paxton said 
wednesday 
a local grocery store gave away more than 100 turkeys this week 
to the striking employees to help them through thanksgiving 
local 12 which also represents workers at the toledo jeep 
plants has started a program called adopt a teledyne family 
union members are being encouraged to give presents and other help 
to teledyne families with children 
paxton said most of the 130 members of united auto workers local 
12 who went on strike in february feel that the walkout has gone on 
for too long teledyne hourly employees walked off the job after 
working eight months without a contract at the manufacturer of 
engines that power military missiles 
a federal mediator is involved but no new talks have been 
scheduled and the company has hired some replacement workers 
a telephone message that a reporter left at the companys 
offices was not immediately returned 
workers at four other teledyne plants in the united states also 
are on strike 
david bosworth president of the unions teledyne unit said the 
union wants the company to continue paying health insurance to 
employees after they retire 
in addition teledyne wants to cap cost of living increases for 
workers who earn 1350 an hour it also is seeking job 
description changes that would allow some positions to be combined 
union members receive 100 a week in strike pay some members 
have wives who work others have had to dip into their savings to 
support their families 
i know of families that are hurting real bad members of this 
unit never expected to be on strike this long i thought wed have 
it over by now bosworth said 
the mood was somber at a meeting wednesday where workers 
listened to the latest news about the strike and picked up food 
donated by other unions 
i wish i had some good news but i dont have any bosworth 
told more than 100 workers 
